The 3.0.3-test3 patch includes:

>+ #ifdef HAVE_LSTAT
>  		lstat(fn, &sbuf);
>+ #else
>+ 		stat(fn, &sbuf);
>+ #endif

but system.h says:

>#ifndef HAVE_LSTAT
># define lstat stat
>#endif

so there is no need for that sort of conditional.

-zefram

